			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Can bards be tanks?<a name="21057"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 12 04 4:46 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Depends entirely on who you are comparing the bard to. At 60+ I highly doubt it, but someone can comment on that.
<br />

<br />
Under 30 or so - absolutely if you have gear better than your groups traditional tank class.
<br />

<br />
With some pretty good gear, I was a better tank than the tank classes I grouped with in my 40s in LDON. I could hold aggro easily with a chant twisted in so long as they didnt taunt. It was FAR easier for our healer to have me be MA, bc the warrior/pally/sks were getting eaten (they probably were PL'ed and didnt have any defense or had horrible gear). That has changed now that Im in my 50s though, even though I have some decent stuff, i'm not as good as the tank classes for obvious reasons.
<br />

<br />
In my experience up to 50 its been **Entirely gear and skill dependent.** After 50, seems our tanking abilities are far inferior, maybe some AA will help. </span></td>
			</tr><tr>
