			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Can bards be tanks?<a name="21063"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 12 04 5:04 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>As a rule, we have significantly lower AC and HP at higher level.  We also lack an ability to taunt and since our songs are coded to have lower agro than similar spells, it is very difficult for a bard at high level to grab and hold agro while serious DPS classes are at work.  On top of that, the races that bards can be generally are not stun resistant which means songs get interrupted a lot when you try to tank.
<br />

<br />
Bottom line: Bards CAN tank.  I would put them below wariors, paladins, shadowknights, and monks for certain.  Maybe below rangers and beastlords too - depends on the gear.  Don't know about berzerkers.
<br />

<br />
EDIT: Just thought I would add -- with full buffs I have around 6800 HP and close to 1500 AC.  On normal LDON adventures, I will off-tank adds with no problem at all for my regular group whose healers are a druid and a shaman.  On hard adventures, I wouldn't dream of doing that.  I've been quadded for close to 4K HP damage in 1 second on hard - it's rare but it happens.  I leave the tanking to our warrior against those guys.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
