				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Can bards be tanks?<a name="21836"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 17 04 10:34 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I've been tankinng a lot lately in LDON with Bardtail.  It started out really when I decided to put my drum away and pull out my second weapon to raise my weapon skills, which were LOW.  I hit lvl 45 and got Jonthan's Provocation.  That song, btw, rocks imo.  I put my silver chitin handwraps on and I figure I'm pushing about 70% haste (someone correct me if I'm wrong).  With dual wield and 70% haste I found I was pulling aggro from every other melee class out there.  The only exception being a good SK.  They can get and hold aggro from me very well.  But pally, ranger, warrior, I pull aggro from them all the time.  So I decided to just pull and MT unless there are arguments from the group.  It's been going well in mid 40's LDON groups.  I like to make the cleric earn my mana song anyway. <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />  
<br />

<br />
As a result my weapons skills have flown up like crazy.  Probably 40 points or more.  It's been nice, and yes, I still twist group haste, villa's celerity, mana song, while I'm playing my self haste.  So I'd say that we can tank, although I certainly don't think we are as good at it as other classes.  It's a nice change of pace though for me.  
<br />

<br />
Incidentally, last night I was looking over my gear and decided I should upgrade a lot of my ornate gold chainmail stuff I'd been wearing forever.  I was frugal and upped my stamina/strength by about 30-40 each at the sacrifice of 70 charisma.  I was charisma top heavy at 214 anyway, so I figured I could spare some.  I went to bed without getting a chance to try it out.  I can't wait to get home tonight and head in to a LDON swinging my troubadour's mace and symphonic scimitar like crazy!</span></td>
