				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Can bards be tanks?<a name="21845"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 17 04 11:16 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Before lvl 45 you can tank no problem.  Often at that lvl, you out aggro tanks a lot anyway.  But higher levels I feel it's not the best idea.  I'm a 56 bard.  I've tanked in an LDoN twice before, once successfully, and once I couldn't hold aggro for anything.  It was a caster heavy group with 2 wizzys, so I got out my drum and we rooted and DoT'd and nuked.  In that case it worked out WAY better than my pathetic attempts at tanking. Ever since then, if I'm asked to tank, I look at the group makeup, and if it's caster heavy we root n' nuke/DoT.  In my case with my average gear, it's the more effienct way to go. Yes, you can tank while singing your DoT's, but why not just root it and save the cleric's mana?  Often the cleric will then have enough mana to nuke also.</span></td>
