				<td colspan="2"><span>Heh.  I can sympathize.  I had a heck of a time learning how to run in those small circles.  I tried doing more of an eliptical shape and timing my song to go off at one of the ends when I was closer to the mobs.  But invariably after every kite I was sitting down with my Hymn song going to recover.  I can't even count how many lag deaths I had though too.  One second of lag can be crucial for me.  3 seconds and I'm a goner for sure!  Keep at it though.  It's a rush to see multiple mobs start dropping one after another as you run away scott free. <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /></span></td>
