				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Can bards be tanks?<a name="21861"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 17 04 11:56 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>As others here have mentioned...
<br />

<br />
Yep we definitely can be tanks and I do it often, but our aggro control is not as desirable as some, but with the right people in your group, you shouldn't have a ton of problems.  As well we just aren't nearly as efficient at soaking up hits as other real tanks.
<br />

<br />
I'm not a raid guild bard and have about as much success as I want though when I do lose aggro I can't just snap it back.  Emphasize HPs and AC and you should do fine.  And like one person mentioned above, I find that emphasizing HPs and AC has given me a TON of versatility, particularly in terms of bailing out my group from my own mistakes (like opening a door in Tak with a mob facing me as I got too close and could train myself and get the crowd under control).</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
